    <text id="B0214T">
        <front id="d2">
            <div1 type="summary" id="d3">
                <p>McDonnell sends a form back to Jackson for correction.</p>
            </div1>
        </front>

        <body id="d4">
            <div1 type="letter" id="d5">
                <head>
                    Bureau <abbr expan="Refugees, Freedmen and Abandoned Lands">R. F. &amp; A.
                        L.</abbr><lb/>Head <abbr expan="Quarters">Qrs</abbr> 9<hi rend="super">t</hi>
                    Sub <abbr expan="District">Dist.</abbr>
                    <abbr expan="Virginia">Va.</abbr>
                    <name type="recipient">Mr. <abbr expan="Thomas">Thos.</abbr> P.
                        Jackson<lb/>Agent<lb/>Staunton, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                </head>

                <opener>
                    <dateline>
                        <date value="1867-12-31"><abbr expan="December">Dec.</abbr> 31st 1867</date>
                        <name type="place">Winchester, <abbr expan="Virginia">Va</abbr></name>
                    </dateline>
                    <salute>Sir</salute>
                </opener>

                <p>I return herewith Receipt Roll for clothing issued to destitute freedpeople. The
                    Rolls are required in <hi rend="underline">duplicate</hi>. The signature to <hi
                        rend="underline">certificate</hi> must be made by me, as the articles are
                        <unclear>borne</unclear> on my Property Return and reported as issued by me.</p>

                <p>Please leave the <hi rend="underline">heading</hi> blank, the body of Roll is
                    correct, and is all that is required.</p>

                <p>As my Returns await your correction of this &amp; its return with duplicate,
                    please send it back with as little delay as possible.</p>

                <closer>
                    <salute>Very Respectfully<lb/>Your <abbr expan="Obedient">Obed</abbr> Servant</salute>
                    <signed>John A. McDonnell<lb/><abbr expan="Captain">Capt</abbr> &amp; <abbr
                            expan="Sub Assistant Commissioner">S.A.C.</abbr></signed>
                </closer>
            </div1>
        </body>
    </text>
